  "texts": [
    "Figure 5 shows the raw text from new maintenance problem, the text after preprocessing, the extracted keywords, and how problems in the historical MWOs are matched with the keywords.",
    "In this instance, we see how the word had appears in many maintenance problems.",
    "If we use this approach to determine how close the existing maintenance problem is to the new problem, we could end up getting many records that are irrelevant due to the presence of an unrelated keyword, a stop word that might have slipped through, or even a technical word that is not pertinent to the meaning of the text.",
    "To address this, we use the Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF) method to find the most common terms.",
    "The TF-IDF implementation in Python involves transforming all the text from the maintenance problem attribute into a feature matrix."
